SIMPLE: emptiness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Emptiness
<hw>Emp"ti*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Empty</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of being empty; absence of contents; void
space; vacuum; <as>as, the <ex>emptiness</ex> of a vessel;
<ex>emptiness</ex> of the stomach.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Want of solidity or substance; unsatisfactoriness;
inability to satisfy desire; vacuity; hollowness; <as>as, the
<ex>emptiness</ex> of earthly glory</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Want of knowledge; lack of sense; vacuity of
mind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Eternal smiles his <qex>emptiness</qex> betray.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The sins of <qex>emptiness</qex>, gossip, and spite.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Emption</ent>⟦br⟧
